snippet: United Nations negotiators presented Libya’s warring factions on Monday with a proposal for forming a unity government.
abstract: United National negotiators present proposal to form unity government to Libya's two rival governments in effort to end fighting between their military forces; plan calls for council of ministers headed by prime minister based in Tripoli.
lead_paragraph: United Nations negotiators presented Libya’s warring factions on Monday with a proposal for forming a unity government.

headline.main: Libya: Plan Presented for Sharing Power
headline.print_headline: Middle East; Libya: Plan Presented for Sharing Power
